args:
Joachim and Noelle make for Chanzelia as
envoys to negotiate with Chelle for a shipment
of manacasters. But before they can complete
the deal, the Empire—now allied with Barthe—
appears on the scene with bad intentions.
Mm? Oh, Noelle. I've been expecting you.\nHave you come with orders from HQ?
Y-yes, ma'am. Er, that's...one letter.\nBut I, um...also have a second one.
Well, isn't this my lucky day? Let's see here.
What's up, Kirsty? You look half-nauseous.
One is from HQ, the other from Litvinov.\nThey both say more or less the same thing.
Litvinov... He's that ＂certain someone.＂\nThe one who's plotting to excise the rot\nof corruption from our nation's core.

That aside, two secret missives coming
from two different senders at the same
time...with the exact same contents? 
Smells like we have some work to do.
Heh, a shrewd guess. You're right: \nI have new orders for you and Noelle.
Yes, you. It's a bit of a departure from your\nusual messenger work, but I'm confident\nthat you'll manage.
I, um, really don't know if I'm cut out for\nanything other than delivering letters.\nEr, not that I even do THAT all that...well.

Have some confidence, soldier! Besides,
I care more about your diligence and
sincerity than I do about your past
accomplishments.
I expect great things from the both of you.
And the weight of those expectations\nis crushing me.
...So that's why ya came to the boss?
Our orders are to negotiate with the ruler\nof Chanzelia for the import of the ancient\nmanacaster weapons she's engineered.
Which is CLEARLY above our pay grade.\nThe prince is the only chance we've got.
I make for a poor lifeline when all I can do\nis arrange a meeting with my sister.
That's all we're asking. Past that,\nit's Svenitla's problem.
Well then! If you've come to negotiate\nwith me, I'd prefer to dispense with the\ndeadweight in the room.
Well that's...harsh. But I suppose we can\nstep outside until you're finish—

Wait. I'd like for {player_name}
to remain here as an impartial third
party familiar with both sides of
the negotiations.
Having someone in the room with no skin\nin the game should let things go smoothly.
Eee hee hee! Oh, well played INDEED!\nThough I don't know that your quick wit\nwill avail you of much in this case.
Meaning we have yet to even reach\nthe negotiating stage.

Delicious as it is to leave you guessing,
I have other things I must attend to today:
Barthe, you see, has ALSO approached me
about a trade deal.

Last I checked, you were in a cease-fire
agreement, yes? Perhaps they've merely
been using that time to shore up their
forces.
Bottom line, Barthe is looking to purchase\nour manacasters. May I presume you came\nto me for much the same reason?
I'll thank you not to jump to conclusions.\nHave I said one word about signing a deal\nwith Barthe? Hmmmm?
No, I very politely sent them on their merry\nway, for I have no intention of exporting\nmanacasters to ANYONE at present.
So, uh, are you also sending US\non our merry way?
I am indeed. Now mind you, I certainly\nwouldn't mind the opportunity to get a\nfoothold in North Grastaea...
But my manacasters are a trump card I\ndon't intend to play for penny-ante stakes.
The only way someone's getting at them\nis if I trust them down to their very core.
So it comes down to trust, eh?
Bad news, guys! We've got imperials\nmarching on our position!
You're not seriously asking me, are you?\nAnyway, it ain't just the Empire this time.
Based on their banners and uniforms, they\nappear to be with the Barthe faction that\nwishes to dispense with the cease-fire.
Goodness, they are NOT eager to take no\nfor an answer on those manacasters.
Yeah, but why's the Empire with 'em?
Perhaps they had better luck sweet-talking\nDyrenell's people than they did with me.
They likely claimed that I only refused to\nsell because I plan to give them all\naway to New Alberia.
And they'd buy that load'a bull?
You would be surprised what people will\nbelieve if you state a vaguely plausible\ncase loudly enough.
Okay, so what's our move? We clearly\nain't gonna stand around and watch them\nchumps march down main street, yeah?
I don't see what choice we have but to\nintercept them. Let's hurry back to the\nsquad standing by outside the city gates!
My, but you ARE an eager beaver!\nI almost didn't have a chance to lend you\nthis before you ran off.
Wait, this is a caster. Don't you only\nhand these things out to folks you\n＂trust down to your very core＂?
Which is why I'm only LENDING it to you.\nBut show you me know how to use it, and\nI might just start to trust you for real.
Can't turn down an offer like that. Thanks.
Rest assured, my little kittens will be\nwatching closely, so do show me you have\nconviction enough to deserve my trust.
Sir, we've gotten word from our scouts that\nthe enemy force approaching from the\nsoutheast numbers ten times our own!
Wow. Ten is...a lot. We may be just a\ntouch outclassed on this one.
I know this is waaay beyond what you\nsigned up for, but you mind lending us a\nhand here, {player_name}?
Of course! I wouldn't abandon you.\nAnd with the Empire involved, this is as\nmuch our problem as yours. We're in.
Appreciate it! And lookee there.\nTheir vanguard's already arrived.

I'm usually not much for the brutal
beatdown, but we don't have a choice if
we wanna get out of this in one piece—
so let's get to it, folks!
